gomodel:SYNGO_2117  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In Figure 4, Shisa9 is demonstrated to modulate the paired-pulse-ratio of AMPAR-mediated synaptic transmission. Using hippocampal CA1 (low Shisa9 expression) and dentage gyrus (high Shisa9 expression) cells from wildtype and knockout mice, combined with over-expression of Shisa9, Figure 4 demonstrates Shisa9 modulates the paired-pulse-ratio of AMPAR-mediated synaptic transmission.\n\nIn Figure 1D, Shisa9 is shown to interact with AMPAR by IP+westernblot.\n\nIn Figure 3, Shisa9 overexpression in Xenopus laevis oocytes modulates AMPAR mediated currents (figure's evidence from this model system not annotated in \"evidence tracking\").. Experimental description: paper literal;\n\n\"We recorded from acute hippocampal brain slices of wild-type, CKAMP44-overexpressing, and knockout (KO) mice\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2117" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

